issue.title: [Feature] Ability to exclude workspace projects from extension
issue.body:
# 🚀 Feature request

What do you want to be added?
The ability to add a block list to my workspace that prevents libraries from showing up in the launch packager menu

## What scenarios will this solve?
I have several projects in my workspace and only one of them is the application, the rest are support libraries... a few of them have a storybook/test harness app to develop independently of the main app... 

What will this allow you to do? Will this benefit other developers?
It will save me time from accidentally starting the wrong packager without having to drop the project from my workspace.

comment.body: Feature is completed, thanks for the great suggestion!

issue.title: [Bug] Restart of debugger disables the breakpoint on every alternate restart on vscode 1.78(latest version)

labels.name: js-debug-related
labels.description: This issue is related to depended extension vscode-js-debug

issue.body:
# 🐛 What is the bug? How can we reproduce it?

Please put here any steps, code or any information that can help us
reproduce the error on our side so we can fix it:

1. Click on Run and Debug with the below configuration
2. {
            "name": "Debug iOS Hermes",
            "request": "launch",
            "type": "reactnativedirect",
            "cwd": "${workspaceFolder}",
            "platform": "ios"
        },
3. Once the debugger gets connected, try to restart the debugger the breakpoints are disabled(shows as unbound breakpoint)
4. When you try to restart again it gets connected.
5. But the same behaviour is seen for every alternate restart.

## Expected behavior

What were you expecting to happen?

The breakpoints should always be hit and should not get disabled.

## Debug output

<details>
<summary>Debug Console</summary>

```text

PASTE OUTPUT OF DEBUG CONSOLE (View -> Toggle Debug Console)

```
</details>

<details>
<summary>React Native output channel</summary>

```text

PASTE OUTPUT OF REACT-NATIVE OUTPUT CHANNEL (View -> Toggle Output -> Select React-Native in ListBox)

```
</details>


<details>
<summary>Developer Tools console</summary>

```text

PASTE OUTPUT OF DEVELOPER TOOLS CONSOLE (Help -> Toggle Developer Tools -> Select Console tab)

```
</details>


## Environment

Please tell us about your system and your project:

* `npx react-native doctor` or `npx expo doctor` if your project is using Expo:

```text
PASTE OUTPUT OF `npx react-native doctor` or `npx expo doctor`
```

* `envinfo`:

```text
PASTE OUTPUT OF `npx envinfo`
```

* React Native Tools extension version: v1.11.0
* Expo SDK version (if applicable): VERSION

comment.body:
Hey @mousumikundu , after investigation, the vscode debug adapter is not support restart as default, so it will be executed disconnect request and attach request, when you click restart button twice.
For now we do not have plan to enable restart request when init debug adapter request and handle restart request in extension, so it should be as design for current scenario.
But we will add this to the backlog and will do some investigations in the future.
